### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Direct Debit Sandbox — HTTP Request Collection
### Works with: IntelliJ HTTP Client  |  VS Code REST Client extension
###
### SCENARIO CHEAT SHEET (last 3 digits of debitAccount drive the outcome):
###
###   TRANSIENT (retry-aware):
###   001  →  Always success
###   002  →  Fail attempt 0, succeed on retry 1
###   003  →  Fail attempts 0–1, succeed on retry 2
###
###   PERMANENT FAILURES:
###   100  →  General failure
###   101  →  Insufficient funds
###   104  →  Duplicate transaction
###   107  →  Invalid credentials
###   110  →  Duplicate transaction (internal)
###   111  →  Inconclusive
###   121  →  Not allowed
###   131  →  Timeout
###   515  →  Account holder not found
###   527  →  Resource not found
###   529  →  Insufficient balance / limit exceeded
###   682  →  Internal error
###   779  →  Resource temporarily locked
###
###   PRE-APPROVAL:
###   004  →  Pre-approval pending (response code 04)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Shared variables — change these once to affect every request below
@baseUrl      = http://localhost:8080
@transflowId  = 82d726a2-4b42-11ee-be56-0242ac120009
@apiKey       = b76d1751-7b10-423e-8ed9-3c6b68ef7a02
@country      = RW
@merchantId   = c64bf5f9-f147-4232-8d00-f28105823d6a
@productId    = ff469300-0a9f-43cc-92ca-25e0b75dfe18
@callbackUrl  = https://webhook.site/25d15f54-20af-47a5-af23-5931dff0378e

@mandateId = e3dddcd7-280f-402b-af85-94605a7d9d3a


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. PROVISION
###    Register the callback URL for a merchant + product.
###    Do this FIRST — all subsequent callbacks are sent to this URL.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1a. Register callback (happy path)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}",
  "retryAttempts": 3,
  "skipFactor": 1,
  "daysToDebitDayNotice": "1,3"
}

###

### 1b. Update callback URL (call again with a different URL — overwrites the old one)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "https://webhook.site/updated-url"
}

###

### 1c. Missing credentials — expect responseCode 107
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId:
x-key:

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. SUBSCRIBE
###    Creates a recurring subscription.
###    Returns 03 immediately. Preapproval callback fires after 2s,
###    transaction callback fires after 7s — to the provisioned URL.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2a. Monthly mobile money — success scenario (account ends 001)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_001",
  "debitNotificationAccount": "0241234001",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true,
  "notificationStatus": true,
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "3" },
    { "name": "skipFactor", "value": "1" }
  ]
}

###

### 2b. Weekly debit with end date
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "25.00",
  "frequencyType": "WEEKLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "endDate": "2027-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "09:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_002"
}

###

### 2c. Insufficient funds scenario (account ends 101)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234101",
  "debitAmount": "200.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "14:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_003"
}

###

### 2d. Duplicate reference — expect responseCode 104
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
