  "preApprovalId": "{{preApprovalId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "9999999999",
  "channel": "BANK",
  "country": "GH"
}

###

### 16c. Cancel — already cancelled — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/pre-authorization/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "preApprovalId": "{{preApprovalId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "country": "GH"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 17. SUBSCRIPTION TRIGGER DEBIT — RETRY CHECK
###     Demonstrates the retry-in-progress guard.
###     If the subscription has a PROCESSING transaction, the call is blocked.
###     Subscribe first (2a), then immediately call trigger before the
###     callback (7 s) resolves — expect the "retries in progress" error.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 17a. Trigger while PROCESSING — expect responseCode 100 (retries in progress)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/trigger-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_2026_001",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 18. SUBSCRIBE — INVALID CHANNEL / DATE VALIDATION
