### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 23. DAILY SUBSCRIPTION — VALIDATION GUARDS
###     DAILY subscriptions have two extra rules:
###       1. notificationStatus cannot be true (no need to notify on daily debits)
###       2. retryAttempts cannot exceed 1 (a retry happens the next day = next cycle)
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 23a. DAILY + notificationStatus=true — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "10.00",
  "frequencyType": "DAILY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "08:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_DAILY_NOTIFY_ERR",
  "notificationStatus": true
}

###

### 23b. DAILY + retryAttempts=3 in config — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "10.00",
  "frequencyType": "DAILY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "08:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_DAILY_RETRY_ERR",
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "3" }
  ]
}

###

### 23c. DAILY + retryAttempts=1 in config — valid (1 is the max allowed for DAILY)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "10.00",
  "frequencyType": "DAILY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "08:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_DAILY_RETRY_OK",
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "1" }
  ]
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 24. CONFIG FALLBACK FROM PROVISION
###     If no configuration list is sent with subscribe, the values
###     provisioned in /provision (retryAttempts, skipFactor, etc.) are used.
###     Steps: 1) run 1a (provision with retryAttempts=3), 2) run 24a (subscribe
###     with no configuration), 3) check the stored record — retryAttempts should be 3.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 24a. Subscribe without configuration — defaults taken from provision
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_DEFAULT_CONFIG",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true
}

###

### 24b. Check the subscription record — configuration should show retryAttempts=3 from provision
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/retrieve/details/thirdpartyreferenceno
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_DEFAULT_CONFIG",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 25. RETRY SIMULATION — TRANSIENT FAILURE SCENARIOS
###     Account suffix 002: fails attempt 0, succeeds on attempt 1.
###     Account suffix 003: fails attempts 0 and 1, succeeds on attempt 2.
###     After subscribing, wait for the automatic RetryScheduler (fires every 30s)
###     to pick up the FAILED transaction and fire the next attempt.
###     Use /debug/store (19a) to watch status change: FAILED → RETRYING → SUCCESS.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 25a. Subscribe with account ending 002 (fail once, then succeed)
###      Provision must set triggerDebitStatus=true and retryAttempts >= 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234002",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_RETRY_002",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true,
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "2" }
  ]
}

###

### 25b. Subscribe with account ending 003 (fail twice, succeed on 3rd attempt)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234003",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_RETRY_003",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true,
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "3" }
  ]
}

###

### 25c. Check transaction status after retry cycle (wait 30–90s for scheduler to fire)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transaction/check-status
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "reference": "REF_RETRY_002",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "mandateId": "<<replace with mandateId from 25a response>>"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 26. RETRY COLLISION GUARD — trigger-debit blocked while RETRYING
###     Step 1: Subscribe with account 003 (fails twice → 2 retries needed).
###     Step 2: Wait 30s for the first retry to start (status → RETRYING).
###     Step 3: While status is RETRYING, immediately call trigger-debit.
###             Expect responseCode 100: "A retry is already in progress..."
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 26a. Trigger debit while scheduler has set status to RETRYING — expect blocked
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/trigger-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_RETRY_003",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 27. EXHAUSTED STATUS — all retries consumed without success
###     Subscribe with account 101 (always fails) and retryAttempts=2.
###     After 2 scheduler cycles (~60s) the transaction should reach EXHAUSTED.
###     An EXHAUSTED transaction is terminal — the scheduler will never pick it up again.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 27a. Subscribe with always-fail account + limited retries
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234101",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_EXHAUST_101",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true,
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "2" }
  ]
}

###

### 27b. Check status after ~60s — expect status EXHAUSTED
POST {{baseUrl}}/transaction/check-status
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "reference": "REF_EXHAUST_101",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "mandateId": "<<replace with mandateId from 27a response>>"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 28. CHANNEL ALIASING — VODAFONE → TELECEL (GH only)
###     In Ghana, Vodafone rebranded to Telecel. Sending "VODAFONE" as the
###     channel with x-country: GH is silently remapped to TELECEL internally.
###     The subscription is created successfully; check /debug/store to confirm
###     the stored channel value is "TELECEL", not "VODAFONE".
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 28a. Subscribe with channel=VODAFONE in GH — expect success, channel stored as TELECEL
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: GH

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "10.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "10:00",
  "channel": "VODAFONE",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_VODAFONE_ALIAS"
}

###

### 28b. Check the stored subscription — channel field should be TELECEL
GET {{baseUrl}}/debug/store
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: GH
